1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,300


2
00:00:01,100 --> 00:00:03,930
Hey, all you viewers out there!

3
00:00:03,930 --> 00:00:07,270
When you're watchin' Fairy Tail, make sure to keep the room nice and bright,

4
00:00:07,270 --> 00:00:09,260
and sit back from the screen, 'kay?

5
00:00:10,690 --> 00:00:12,860
Previously on Fairy Tail!

6
00:00:13,070 --> 00:00:18,280
Phantom's Magical Giant has activated and is trying to cast Abyss Break to destroy all of Magnolia!

7
00:00:18,580 --> 00:00:23,960
And fierce battles with the Element 4 have begun, as they wait to ambush us after we broke inside!

8
00:00:23,960 --> 00:00:27,210
In one battle, Mira has been taken hostage, and when Elfman sees her...

9
00:00:27,510 --> 00:00:29,560
Let my sister go!

10
00:00:49,220 --> 00:00:53,630
It'll be all right! I'll yell it out countless times.

11
00:00:53,630 --> 00:00:58,700
I believe your every tomorrow will be shining.

12
00:00:58,700 --> 00:01:01,050
The intersection of all people

13
00:01:01,050 --> 00:01:03,660
whose dreams have come true is one point:

14
00:01:03,660 --> 00:01:08,290
Never giving up.  And that's why we're not gonna lose!

15
00:01:08,290 --> 00:01:13,470
When it seems like you'll be blown away by the headwinds,

16
00:01:13,470 --> 00:01:15,620
grasp this hand, try to take a chance.

17
00:01:15,620 --> 00:01:18,890
Because you're not alone anymore, got it?

18
00:01:22,010 --> 00:01:24,000
Go forward, more and more!

19
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:26,520
Don't give up on your awesome dream!

20
00:01:26,520 --> 00:01:27,780
That's right, don't cry!

21
00:01:27,780 --> 00:01:29,250
Move on, my way!

22
00:01:29,250 --> 00:01:31,630
Now, with the light shining down upon you.

23
00:01:31,630 --> 00:01:33,710
Don't even think about something like giving up!

24
00:01:33,710 --> 00:01:36,140
Even if you trade being hurt again for strength.

25
00:01:36,140 --> 00:01:41,630
Your eyes, always looking straight ahead,

26
00:01:41,630 --> 00:01:45,910
can surely see the light!

27
00:02:06,110 --> 00:02:09,150
Huh? When did I get home?

28
00:02:09,150 --> 00:02:11,100
I could have sworn Phantom was attacking...

29
00:02:12,040 --> 00:02:15,710
Was it all a dream?

30
00:02:15,710 --> 00:02:17,650
Yup, that's right. All just a dream.

31
00:02:17,940 --> 00:02:20,120
So go right back to sleep...

32
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:21,650
Nice body!

33
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:23,080
Destroy the moon!

34
00:02:23,080 --> 00:02:24,830
This makes no sense!

35
00:02:25,860 --> 00:02:28,200
Hey, isn't something moving?

36
00:02:28,500 --> 00:02:30,290
Drip, drip, drop...

37
00:02:30,290 --> 00:02:32,170
You're freakin' me out!

38
00:02:32,170 --> 00:02:34,210
Drip, drip, drop...

39
00:02:34,210 --> 00:02:36,730
G-Get out...

40
00:02:36,730 --> 00:02:37,860
Lucy!

41
00:02:39,010 --> 00:02:41,720
Are you okay, Lucy?

42
00:02:41,770 --> 00:02:44,010
This is <i>my</i> room!

43
00:02:45,110 --> 00:02:46,490
No, it's not!

44
00:02:46,490 --> 00:02:48,980
Wait, where am I?

45
00:02:51,030 --> 00:02:53,550
A Flower Blooms in the Rain

46
00:02:59,490 --> 00:03:02,530
I-It can't be... This is...

47
00:03:02,530 --> 00:03:04,790
A Full Body Take Over...

48
00:03:04,790 --> 00:03:06,150
Beast Soul!

49
00:03:10,620 --> 00:03:12,670
Non, non, non!

50
00:03:12,670 --> 00:03:14,510
With non of three, you misunderstand me!

51
00:03:14,510 --> 00:03:21,840
I, Monsieur, gave you such a harsh trial for you to finally overcome your difficult past, bonsoir!

52
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:24,690
You are indeed a Man among men, Elfman!

53
00:03:24,690 --> 00:03:28,020
I, Monsieur, believed you could overcome it!

54
00:03:28,780 --> 00:03:29,600
Right?

55
00:03:31,180 --> 00:03:34,680
Well then, if you'll be excusing me...

56
00:03:35,950 --> 00:03:37,580
How dare you!

57
00:03:37,580 --> 00:03:40,510
Plâtre... Sonate!

58
00:03:42,530 --> 00:03:45,730
Non, non, non... Don't let your guard down now.

59
00:03:49,180 --> 00:03:51,690
Non! Non! Non!

60
00:03:51,690 --> 00:03:54,120
Non! Non! Non!

61
00:03:57,220 --> 00:03:58,750
Elfman...

62
00:03:59,280 --> 00:04:01,210
Ooh... Oui...

63
00:04:01,430 --> 00:04:03,710
Je t'aime...

64
00:04:06,050 --> 00:04:09,790
No~n, at least let me fall unconscious!

65
00:04:10,640 --> 00:04:12,280
Elfman!

66
00:04:13,320 --> 00:04:15,290
Au revoir...

67
00:04:21,400 --> 00:04:24,320
So... Can you...

68
00:04:27,270 --> 00:04:29,050
...hear my voice?

69
00:04:34,080 --> 00:04:37,700
Could you have lost your reason again?

70
00:04:39,150 --> 00:04:40,370
Elfman!

71
00:04:44,640 --> 00:04:46,250
I'm sorry, Nee-chan...

72
00:04:47,380 --> 00:04:50,750
You must never have wanted to see me like this again.

73
00:04:51,680 --> 00:04:55,460
Because I wasn't able to control it, Lisanna...

74
00:04:56,040 --> 00:04:58,200
You still have your reason!

75
00:04:58,790 --> 00:05:01,450
But I didn't know what else to do.

76
00:05:02,780 --> 00:05:07,450
I had to get stronger to protect you and Fairy Tail!

77
00:05:10,820 --> 00:05:14,860
Lisanna's death wasn't your fault.

78
00:05:15,440 --> 00:05:19,990
You were trying your best to protect us both back then.

79
00:05:22,550 --> 00:05:24,390
But I failed.

80
00:05:24,690 --> 00:05:26,800
Lisanna died.

81
00:05:32,680 --> 00:05:34,700
I'm still here.

82
00:05:34,700 --> 00:05:35,980
Nee-chan...

83
00:05:36,880 --> 00:05:38,620
We decided together, remember?

84
00:05:38,990 --> 00:05:41,570
To live on in her stead.

85
00:05:41,940 --> 00:05:44,460
To work as hard as we could...

86
00:05:51,160 --> 00:05:55,680
Nee-chan! I'm so glad you're all right!

87
00:05:59,230 --> 00:06:01,150
And how is crying going to help anything?

88
00:06:01,150 --> 00:06:03,330
But!

89
00:06:04,920 --> 00:06:07,600
Thank you, Elfman...

90
00:06:09,840 --> 00:06:11,390
What is it, Nee-chan?

91
00:06:13,100 --> 00:06:16,770
The giant isn't writing as quickly...

92
00:06:18,230 --> 00:06:20,600
The forbidden magic of the four elements...

93
00:06:20,970 --> 00:06:22,600
Abyss Break...

94
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:28,450
The four elements. Fire, water, wind, and earth...

95
00:06:30,210 --> 00:06:34,120
Elfman, how many of the Element 4 are left?

96
00:06:34,120 --> 00:06:35,740
Hmm, um...

97
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:40,370
That'd make two left, I guess?

98
00:06:40,370 --> 00:06:41,120
As I thought!

99
00:06:41,390 --> 00:06:44,690
Each time we get one of them, the giant's movements slow down!

100
00:06:44,690 --> 00:06:46,100
Why is that?

101
00:06:46,670 --> 00:06:50,310
In other words, this giant is powered by the four elements.

102
00:06:50,310 --> 00:06:54,060
If we can defeat all of the Element 4, we can stop the magic!

103
00:06:54,060 --> 00:06:55,180
Really?

104
00:06:55,460 --> 00:06:59,600
Hurry! The remaining two should be somewhere inside the giant!

105
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:00,690
R-Right!

106
00:07:05,790 --> 00:07:09,470
Thank goodness... It looks like Mira's safe.

107
00:07:11,320 --> 00:07:12,240
Cana!

108
00:07:12,240 --> 00:07:13,740
I'm fine.

109
00:07:14,040 --> 00:07:17,830
Focus on the enemy in front of you and protect Fairy Tail!

110
00:07:18,180 --> 00:07:19,910
You don't know when to quit...

111
00:07:22,960 --> 00:07:25,860
Everyone, don't clump together! Spread out and fight!

112
00:07:25,860 --> 00:07:27,380
Right!

113
00:07:27,380 --> 00:07:31,720
It's the women in our guild who are the strong ones...

114
00:07:32,040 --> 00:07:34,240
Oh yeah, where's Loke?

115
00:07:34,240 --> 00:07:37,740
He said something worried him, so he headed to that place.

116
00:07:37,740 --> 00:07:38,990
Say what?

117
00:07:38,990 --> 00:07:40,460
He skipped out?

118
00:07:40,460 --> 00:07:44,560
If Abyss Break is cast, then that place wouldn't be safe either.

119
00:07:44,860 --> 00:07:45,810
I see...

120
00:07:46,110 --> 00:07:48,530
He has good intuition.

121
00:07:51,530 --> 00:07:54,190
I just thought of something good, Happy!

122
00:07:54,190 --> 00:07:55,510
What?

123
00:07:55,510 --> 00:07:59,480
If we beat up Jose, then that'd end the fight, right?

124
00:08:00,580 --> 00:08:02,790
What are you saying?

125
00:08:02,790 --> 00:08:06,190
Jose's just as powerful as our own master!

126
00:08:06,190 --> 00:08:08,290
Someone like you could never beat him, Natsu!

127
00:08:08,290 --> 00:08:12,770
But Gramps isn't here, so who else is gonna?

128
00:08:13,340 --> 00:08:15,900
Natsu, you idiot!

129
00:08:15,900 --> 00:08:19,690
I was trying not to think about it, but you made me remember!

130
00:08:19,690 --> 00:08:20,350
Wha?

131
00:08:20,650 --> 00:08:24,370
That's right... Master's gone... Erza's gone...

132
00:08:24,370 --> 00:08:28,810
No matter what happens in this war, in the end Jose will...

133
00:08:29,850 --> 00:08:31,570
I'm here, aren't I?

134
00:08:33,110 --> 00:08:34,560
Right?

135
00:08:34,560 --> 00:08:36,240
Aye!

136
00:08:37,300 --> 00:08:38,700
Why is it, I wonder?

137
00:08:38,940 --> 00:08:42,180
The master and Erza have more magic power,

138
00:08:42,180 --> 00:08:46,260
but there's something about Natsu that gives everyone hope!

139
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:55,940
The sorrow!

140
00:08:58,500 --> 00:09:02,150
The wings of flame, clipped... Falling to the ground...

141
00:09:02,150 --> 00:09:05,640
Ah, and all that's left is the corpse of a dragon!

142
00:09:06,870 --> 00:09:09,310
Natsu, he's one of the Element 4!

143
00:09:10,950 --> 00:09:13,190
My name is Aria!

144
00:09:14,550 --> 00:09:17,280
I am at the top of the Element 4!

145
00:09:17,280 --> 00:09:19,870
And I have come to hunt me a dragon!

146
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:22,330
A wind wizard?

147
00:09:22,330 --> 00:09:23,980
I'm already used to you guys.

148
00:09:23,980 --> 00:09:26,930
Erigor's nothing compared to him!

149
00:09:40,490 --> 00:09:43,220
Was it raining before?

150
00:09:44,510 --> 00:09:46,600
Drip, drip, drop...

151
00:09:47,790 --> 00:09:53,330
Yes... Juvia is the rain woman, one of the Element 4.

152
00:09:53,330 --> 00:09:55,600
Drip, drip, drop...

153
00:09:55,600 --> 00:09:59,230
You're one of the Element 4?

154
00:09:59,230 --> 00:10:04,340
I never would have thought that two of the elements would have been defeated.

155
00:10:04,340 --> 00:10:08,400
But do not underestimate Juvia and Aria.

156
00:10:08,400 --> 00:10:12,380
Sorry to break it to you, but I don't go easy on people who hurt my friends.

157
00:10:12,380 --> 00:10:16,010
Even if they're women or children...

158
00:10:27,550 --> 00:10:29,360
R-Really?

159
00:10:29,360 --> 00:10:31,690
Juvia gives up then! Goodbye!

160
00:10:31,690 --> 00:10:34,320
Whoa there! What the heck?

161
00:10:37,050 --> 00:10:39,230
What is wrong with Juvia?

162
00:10:39,230 --> 00:10:40,990
Why is my heart beating like this?

163
00:10:40,990 --> 00:10:43,370
Wait, you! Stop the giant!

164
00:10:44,740 --> 00:10:47,030
Juvia wants to make him her's!

165
00:10:47,030 --> 00:10:48,500
Juvia can no longer hold back!

166
00:10:48,500 --> 00:10:50,460
Water Lock!

167
00:10:52,420 --> 00:10:57,120
Oh, no! He's injured! Whatever shall I do?

168
00:10:57,120 --> 00:10:58,760
I must release him quick, or...

169
00:11:03,670 --> 00:11:07,390
He escaped from Juvia's water lock using his own power?

170
00:11:07,950 --> 00:11:10,640
This is the power of an ice wizard...

171
00:11:10,890 --> 00:11:12,190
Exquisite!

172
00:11:13,340 --> 00:11:15,490
Water and ice...

173
00:11:15,490 --> 00:11:17,900
It's like we're bound by fate!

174
00:11:17,900 --> 00:11:21,070
I've finally found you, Juvia's Prince!

175
00:11:22,580 --> 00:11:26,200
Trying for a surprise attack, you bastard!

176
00:11:28,130 --> 00:11:29,500
Ouch!

177
00:11:30,260 --> 00:11:32,150
Why is he stripping?

178
00:11:32,150 --> 00:11:35,000
I-I-I think we should take things more slowly...

179
00:11:35,290 --> 00:11:40,400
I don't want to frighten a woman, but you'd better surrender immediately.

180
00:11:40,400 --> 00:11:42,300
Otherwise you're gonna get hurt!

181
00:11:42,300 --> 00:11:44,140
Ice Make Lance!

182
00:11:47,640 --> 00:11:50,600
Juvia's body is made of water.

183
00:11:51,660 --> 00:11:54,400
Yes... Drip, drip, drop...

184
00:11:55,520 --> 00:11:58,080
That's right... He's an enemy.

185
00:11:58,080 --> 00:12:02,550
Torn apart by strife, that is their tearful fate!

186
00:12:02,850 --> 00:12:04,910
But Juvia will not lose heart!

187
00:12:05,240 --> 00:12:07,370
Farewell, my small blossom of love!

188
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:09,700
Water Slicer!

189
00:12:14,240 --> 00:12:18,280
High powered water jets can even cut through steel.

190
00:12:18,620 --> 00:12:22,180
Underestimate water, and you will regret it.

191
00:12:23,330 --> 00:12:26,050
Ice Make Battle Axe!

192
00:12:26,050 --> 00:12:28,920
Try again and again, but nothing will change.

193
00:12:28,920 --> 00:12:31,950
Against Juvia, physical attacks are ineffective.

194
00:12:31,950 --> 00:12:33,980
Yes... Drip, drip, drop...

195
00:12:34,750 --> 00:12:36,190
She's a tough one...

196
00:12:36,700 --> 00:12:39,010
You cannot defeat Juvia.

197
00:12:39,540 --> 00:12:41,900
You still have a chance to save yourself.

198
00:12:42,260 --> 00:12:45,190
Bring me Lucy Heartfilia, please.

199
00:12:45,650 --> 00:12:49,460
If you do, I will ask my master to withdraw.

200
00:12:50,590 --> 00:12:53,700
Hey, don't give me that crap.

201
00:12:54,190 --> 00:12:57,520
We're both already way past the point of retreating.

202
00:12:59,090 --> 00:13:01,320
And Lucy is our ally!

203
00:13:01,320 --> 00:13:03,680
I'll give up my life before handing her over to you!

204
00:13:05,340 --> 00:13:07,100
Give up his life?

205
00:13:07,100 --> 00:13:08,330
Give up his life?

206
00:13:08,330 --> 00:13:09,690
Give up his life?

207
00:13:09,690 --> 00:13:10,550
A love rival!

208
00:13:10,550 --> 00:13:11,350
A love rival!

209
00:13:11,350 --> 00:13:11,900
A love rival!

210
00:13:11,900 --> 00:13:13,030
A love rival!

211
00:13:13,030 --> 00:13:14,310
A love rival!

212
00:13:17,200 --> 00:13:18,650
What pain!

213
00:13:18,650 --> 00:13:20,510
What harsh fate!

214
00:13:20,510 --> 00:13:23,880
My heart... My heart feels like it's going to rend asunder!

215
00:13:23,880 --> 00:13:24,950
It hurts!

216
00:13:24,950 --> 00:13:25,790
It hurts!

217
00:13:25,790 --> 00:13:27,700
What's the matter? Are you ill?

218
00:13:29,450 --> 00:13:31,700
Juvia will not forgive.

219
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:35,000
Lucy shall not be forgiven!

220
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:46,300
Lucy shall not be forgiven!

221
00:13:49,850 --> 00:13:50,920
Ouch!

222
00:13:50,920 --> 00:13:51,850
Boiling water?

223
00:13:52,190 --> 00:13:54,850
And why are you mad at Lucy?

224
00:13:55,430 --> 00:13:56,930
Ice Make...

225
00:13:59,520 --> 00:14:00,840
It's fast!

226
00:14:00,840 --> 00:14:02,980
My Creation Magic can't keep up!

227
00:14:08,140 --> 00:14:09,530
That was close...

228
00:14:09,760 --> 00:14:13,860
Ever since Juvia was born, she's lived within the rain.

229
00:14:13,860 --> 00:14:17,960
In the rain, there is no one who can defeat Juvia!

230
00:14:18,230 --> 00:14:22,130
Be boiled inside Juvia's jealously!

231
00:14:22,130 --> 00:14:23,840
What?

232
00:14:26,300 --> 00:14:28,590
Ice Make Shield!

233
00:14:29,480 --> 00:14:32,220
What incredible heat! I can't stand it!

234
00:14:32,430 --> 00:14:33,830
I told you already!

235
00:14:33,830 --> 00:14:36,140
Inside the rain is Juvia's world!

236
00:14:36,140 --> 00:14:38,390
No one can defeat Juvia!

237
00:14:42,830 --> 00:14:44,980
He used the steam as a smoke screen?

238
00:14:45,610 --> 00:14:48,600
He's not just a pretty face, he's smart, too.

239
00:14:49,640 --> 00:14:51,490
So amazing...

240
00:14:51,490 --> 00:14:55,010
I don't have time to take a break!

241
00:14:55,010 --> 00:14:57,300
I've got to stop that magic quick!

242
00:14:59,400 --> 00:15:00,370
That's hot!

243
00:15:00,370 --> 00:15:01,770
My skin is burning!

244
00:15:03,540 --> 00:15:04,970
This is the end for you!

245
00:15:05,360 --> 00:15:07,000
Why, you...

246
00:15:08,260 --> 00:15:10,510
He flew straight into the boiling water!

247
00:15:10,510 --> 00:15:13,120
Freeze!

248
00:15:13,120 --> 00:15:14,300
B-But...

249
00:15:15,240 --> 00:15:18,270
Juvia's boiling water was frozen?

250
00:15:18,480 --> 00:15:19,980
And...

251
00:15:22,540 --> 00:15:24,360
That's not... It's not...

252
00:15:24,360 --> 00:15:26,190
Juvia is so embarrassed!

253
00:15:26,190 --> 00:15:29,070
Like this, forever, inside your ice...

254
00:15:29,070 --> 00:15:30,870
Sorry!

255
00:15:32,100 --> 00:15:34,430
He released me from the ice?

256
00:15:34,430 --> 00:15:35,390
Why?

257
00:15:35,880 --> 00:15:37,580
He's too kind!

258
00:15:37,820 --> 00:15:40,370
Let's start over again!

259
00:15:40,370 --> 00:15:45,670
No, I can't. Juvia cannot bring herself to harm you...

260
00:15:45,670 --> 00:15:46,390
Huh?

261
00:15:46,390 --> 00:15:48,590
So you're admitting you can't win against me?

262
00:15:48,870 --> 00:15:50,990
Juvia is stronger than Lucy.

263
00:15:51,320 --> 00:15:54,510
Juvia will be able to protect you.

264
00:15:54,740 --> 00:15:57,880
Protect?  Me?

265
00:15:57,880 --> 00:16:00,240
B-Because...

266
00:16:01,570 --> 00:16:06,230
I-I... l-lo...

267
00:16:06,530 --> 00:16:09,010
Sheesh, now the rain's gotten stronger.

268
00:16:09,010 --> 00:16:11,150
Juvia is frustrated!

269
00:16:11,150 --> 00:16:14,360
Man, this rain is so gloomy...

270
00:16:14,660 --> 00:16:18,080
Gloomy... Gloomy... Gloomy...

271
00:16:19,560 --> 00:16:20,490
What's the matter?

272
00:16:20,920 --> 00:16:24,750
He's no different than all the others!

273
00:16:24,750 --> 00:16:27,630
You're all the same!

274
00:16:26,700 --> 00:16:27,630
What?

275
00:16:27,880 --> 00:16:31,290
Juvia has no need for love anymore!

276
00:16:32,480 --> 00:16:34,730
I'll freeze it again!

277
00:16:34,730 --> 00:16:37,470
It won't freeze? Is it even hotter than before?

278
00:16:37,770 --> 00:16:41,680
Love... Who needs love?!

279
00:16:47,600 --> 00:16:51,150
I wish Juvia would take a long vacation...

280
00:16:51,150 --> 00:16:54,030
When she's around it's always raining and gloomy.

281
00:16:54,730 --> 00:16:55,360
Yes.

282
00:16:56,560 --> 00:16:58,280
Juvia is a rain woman.

283
00:16:58,890 --> 00:17:01,490
Man, how gloomy!

284
00:17:01,490 --> 00:17:03,650
What's this?

285
00:17:09,210 --> 00:17:11,210
Why is it always raining?

286
00:17:11,210 --> 00:17:14,160
I can't go fishing or camping with you around.

287
00:17:14,160 --> 00:17:17,970
I'm sorry. But Juvia doesn't know what else to do...

288
00:17:18,270 --> 00:17:20,380
I can't stand this gloom anymore.

289
00:17:20,380 --> 00:17:22,600
Let's break up, okay?

290
00:17:23,350 --> 00:17:25,410
This rain is really gloomy.

291
00:17:25,410 --> 00:17:27,690
The longer it rains, the gloomier it gets!

292
00:17:27,690 --> 00:17:29,960
Man, this is gloomy.

293
00:17:29,960 --> 00:17:32,880
Rain sucks. It's so gloomy.

294
00:17:33,150 --> 00:17:36,470
Juvia is nothing but a gloomy rain woman!

295
00:17:36,470 --> 00:17:41,800
And yet Phantom Lord accepted Juvia for who she is!

296
00:17:41,800 --> 00:17:46,330
Juvia is one of the Element 4! A Phantom Wizard!

297
00:17:47,590 --> 00:17:49,000


298
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:50,960
I'm not gonna lose!

299
00:17:50,960 --> 00:17:53,130
Not to Phantom!

300
00:17:59,420 --> 00:18:01,100
He even froze the rain?

301
00:18:01,100 --> 00:18:02,180
What incredible magical power!

302
00:18:02,180 --> 00:18:05,180
Ice Geyser!

303
00:18:11,470 --> 00:18:12,440
I've lost...

304
00:18:13,250 --> 00:18:15,480
It's all over now... Everything...

305
00:18:15,480 --> 00:18:19,950
Juvia, like a raindrop, will fall to the ground, and scatter into tiny fragments...

306
00:18:21,200 --> 00:18:26,240
A fitting end to an unwanted rain woman...

307
00:18:27,030 --> 00:18:31,080
Farewell, my gloomy self...

308
00:18:33,130 --> 00:18:34,720
Don't let go of my hand!

309
00:18:34,720 --> 00:18:36,300
I'm not letting you fall!

310
00:18:39,760 --> 00:18:41,580
Why did you save Juvia?

311
00:18:41,580 --> 00:18:42,790
Beats me.

312
00:18:42,790 --> 00:18:44,260
Anyway, get some sleep.

313
00:18:45,280 --> 00:18:47,880
Why did he...

314
00:18:47,880 --> 00:18:50,440
So, finally cooled down?

315
00:18:55,990 --> 00:18:56,940
Huh?

316
00:18:59,730 --> 00:19:02,570
The rain has stopped...

317
00:19:02,870 --> 00:19:05,330
Oh, it's finally clearing up.

318
00:19:05,940 --> 00:19:08,790
These are... clear skies...

319
00:19:09,390 --> 00:19:11,050
I've never seen them before...

320
00:19:11,050 --> 00:19:12,690
Really?

321
00:19:13,630 --> 00:19:14,920
Nice, huh?

322
00:19:14,920 --> 00:19:16,340
Clear skies are great.

323
00:19:19,580 --> 00:19:23,250
Yes... They're beautiful, truly...

324
00:19:24,260 --> 00:19:27,310
So, up for round 2?

325
00:19:30,250 --> 00:19:33,400
Hey! What's the matter?

326
00:19:33,400 --> 00:19:34,690
Hang in there!

327
00:19:34,690 --> 00:19:36,770
Hey! Hey!

328
00:19:40,150 --> 00:19:44,510
A lot of time has passed, but the magic hasn't activated yet!

329
00:19:44,510 --> 00:19:46,320
This is bad for my heart.

330
00:19:46,320 --> 00:19:47,700
How long until it's over?

331
00:19:47,700 --> 00:19:51,500
Wait, isn't that giant moving turtlish?

332
00:19:51,500 --> 00:19:54,010
Huh? Turtl-what?

333
00:19:54,010 --> 00:19:56,650
She means it's moving more slowly, I think.

334
00:19:56,650 --> 00:19:58,460
Try speaking so we can understand you!

335
00:19:58,460 --> 00:20:01,500
I like talking this way!

336
00:20:01,500 --> 00:20:05,260
Natsu and the others inside are doing their best to hold it back, I bet.

337
00:20:06,300 --> 00:20:07,930
All we can do is...

338
00:20:09,640 --> 00:20:14,070
...hold these guys back so they don't get in the way of Natsu and the others!

339
00:20:14,380 --> 00:20:16,450
I guess we should clean them up, then.

340
00:20:16,450 --> 00:20:17,560
Let's go!

341
00:20:17,560 --> 00:20:19,570
Yeah!

342
00:20:19,970 --> 00:20:21,800
Gray!

343
00:20:21,800 --> 00:20:25,070
Elfman! And Mira too?

344
00:20:25,500 --> 00:20:28,450
So this is the third Element 4?

345
00:20:28,450 --> 00:20:31,040
Why does she look so happy?

346
00:20:31,040 --> 00:20:33,870
Beats me. Maybe she's having a nice dream.

347
00:20:34,170 --> 00:20:35,380
Only one left!

348
00:20:35,970 --> 00:20:39,250
If we can defeat one more, we can stop Abyss Break.

349
00:20:39,610 --> 00:20:44,160
The Magic Giant moves using the power of the Element 4.

350
00:20:44,160 --> 00:20:45,520
We can still make it!

351
00:20:45,520 --> 00:20:46,660
We can do it!

352
00:20:49,090 --> 00:20:50,470
I see...

353
00:20:50,470 --> 00:20:52,970
I was put to sleep by Mira...

354
00:20:52,970 --> 00:20:56,140
Oui. This is our emergency hide-out.

355
00:20:56,140 --> 00:20:59,170
I lost my keys...

356
00:20:59,170 --> 00:21:01,990
I guess I was in everyone's way.

357
00:21:01,990 --> 00:21:03,560
No choice then, yeah?

358
00:21:03,560 --> 00:21:05,500
That's not it.

359
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:09,500
We just wanted to protect our friend.

360
00:21:09,500 --> 00:21:12,240
Getting in the way doesn't have anything to do with it.

361
00:21:12,240 --> 00:21:13,670
Reedus...

362
00:21:13,670 --> 00:21:17,360
But that's why I can't just sit here!

363
00:21:17,360 --> 00:21:19,100
I've got to go back!

364
00:21:19,100 --> 00:21:20,660
You can't, Lucy!

365
00:21:20,660 --> 00:21:22,360
Think of what Mirajane...

366
00:21:22,360 --> 00:21:23,280
But...

367
00:21:29,250 --> 00:21:31,210
Oh, no! What is this?

368
00:21:31,210 --> 00:21:33,230
Lucy, stand back!

369
00:21:40,760 --> 00:21:43,380
You do well to remain standing.

370
00:21:43,380 --> 00:21:44,570
Impressive.

371
00:21:44,570 --> 00:21:46,900
Damn you...

372
00:21:46,900 --> 00:21:48,570
What's with this guy?

373
00:21:48,570 --> 00:21:52,030
I've never seen Natsu in such a one-sided fight!

374
00:21:52,290 --> 00:21:57,920
But in the face of my "Airspace" magic, you are powerless!

375
00:21:58,580 --> 00:22:01,000
What the hell is Airspace magic?

376
00:22:03,840 --> 00:22:06,720
Invisible magic! What should we do?

377
00:22:09,630 --> 00:22:12,690
You can still stand, Salamander?

378
00:22:12,690 --> 00:22:15,180
I can't be defeated here.

379
00:22:15,180 --> 00:22:17,890
Because I'm a Fairy Tail wizard!

380
00:22:18,190 --> 00:22:21,790
Now I'm fired up, you bastard!

381
00:23:56,310 --> 00:23:57,600
All right!

382
00:23:57,600 --> 00:24:00,510
Defeat one more, and we stop that magic!

383
00:24:00,510 --> 00:24:01,280
Aye!

384
00:24:01,280 --> 00:24:04,740
But there's still Gajeel and Master Jose.

385
00:24:05,130 --> 00:24:06,790
I forgot!

386
00:24:06,790 --> 00:24:10,030
I wonder if I can get something to eat before fighting them.

387
00:24:10,030 --> 00:24:11,010
Aye!

388
00:24:11,010 --> 00:24:14,290
Then let's search for the kitchen first!

389
00:24:14,290 --> 00:24:16,510
Next time: Wings of Flame!

390
00:24:17,680 --> 00:24:18,680
Isn't that Erza?

391
00:24:18,990 --> 00:24:22,770
Oh, no! If she finds out we're taking a break here, she'll get mad!

392
00:24:22,770 --> 00:24:24,020
Run for it, Happy!

393
00:24:24,020 --> 00:24:25,240
Aye!

